This directory contains a version of the scripts suitable for Checker
Framework developers.  The scripts use locally-compiled .class files in
preference to .jar files, because just creating .class files leads to a
faster edit-compile-test cycle than generating .jar files.


This directory also contains Dockerfiles to create new Docker images for
running Checker Framework tests reproducibly.
To build new Docker images:

  # Obtain Docker credentials
  docker login

  # Create the Docker images, in an empty directory
  mkdir empty-dir
  cd empty-dir
  docker build -f ../Dockerfile-jdk7 -t mdernst/ubuntu-for-cf-jdk7 .
  docker build -f ../Dockerfile-jdk8 -t mdernst/ubuntu-for-cf-jdk8 .
  docker build -f ../Dockerfile-jdkany -t mdernst/ubuntu-for-cf-jdkany .
  cd ..
  rm -rf empty-dir

  # Optionally, list the available images
  # docker images

  # Upload to Docker Hub
  docker push mdernst/ubuntu-for-cf-jdk7
  docker push mdernst/ubuntu-for-cf-jdk8
  docker push mdernst/ubuntu-for-cf-jdkany
